Colouration. ( From colour photograph,
Fig 4
). Generally black and white. Body and appendages white except for proximal halves of antennae, antero-dorsal carapace, ventral branchiostegite, most of first to fourth abdominal segments except posterior part of each pleuron, antero-ventral half of fifth segment, second pereiopods with distal carpus and proximal chela, bases of third to fifth pereiopods and pleopods. Second pereiopod chelae with golden tinge.
